      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/pump-hemolysis-benchmark",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FDA pump hemolysis benchmark validation — 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD predictions of normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against FDA benchmark experimental data at five flow-speed combinations. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 satisfied at all operating points. The supporting UQ campaign (Latin hypercube sampling, n=128) demonstrated that model outputs are insensitive to ±5% perturbations in inlet boundary conditions and fluid viscosity, with coefficient of variation < 3% on RH across all operating points. Full UQ tabulation provided in technical report DOI:10.1115/1.4045878."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/mesh-independence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh independence and discretisation error study",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.2M elements) using Richardson extrapolation. GCI < 2.1% on NIH for medium-to-fine transition; medium mesh selected for production runs. Iterative convergence confirmed at residual < 1e-6 for all equations."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/code-verification-report",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Numerical code verification — manufactured solution benchmarks",
